{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "c4d5e6f7-3456-7890-bcde-f12345678901",
    "name": "Tree-Crown Species Pipeline API",
    "description": "Postman collection for the FastAPI service at app/main.py.\n\n**Run server:**  `uvicorn app.main:app --reload --port 8000`\n\n**Setup in Postman:**\n1. Import this collection and the companion environment file.\n2. Select 'Tree Classification - Local' in the top-right environment selector.\n3. If you set TCP_API_KEY in .env, fill the `api_key` env variable. Otherwise leave it blank — the collection sends the header but the server ignores it when no key is configured.\n\n**Suggested flow (full happy path):**\n  Health → Create project → Upload orthomosaic → Start analyze → Poll job → Clustering overview → Submit labels → Start finalize → Poll job → Get results → Download KMZ\n\nThe `project_id`, `job_id`, and `chosen_k` environment variables are filled by the test scripts attached to the relevant requests, so calls chain automatically when you run them in order.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "apikey",
    "apikey": [
      {
        "key": "key",
        "value": "X-API-Key",
        "type": "string"
      },
      {
        "key": "value",
        "value": "{{api_key}}",
        "type": "string"
      },
      {
        "key": "in",
        "value": "header",
        "type": "string"
      }
    ]
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Meta",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Liveness probe",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/livez",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "livez"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Liveness probe - is the process up. Used by Docker/K8s container healthchecks."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "List detectors",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/detectors",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "v1",
                "detectors"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Show the registered Detectree2 detector .pth weight files, which is the default, and which are present on disk. Pick one as model_key when creating a project."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "List feature-extractors",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/feature-extractors",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "v1",
                "feature-extractors"
              ]
            },
            "description": "List the allowed DINOv2 feature-extractor models (valid `model_name` values for params), each with its description, intended img_size, and which is the default. Use these to populate a model_name picker. Any model_name NOT in this list is rejected with 400 at project creation."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Projects",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Create project",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "// Capture the new project_id into the environment for subsequent requests",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "    const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "    if (body.project_id) {",
                  "        pm.environment.set('project_id', body.project_id);",
                  "        console.log('Saved project_id =', body.project_id);",
                  "    }",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Sanjay Van S3\",\n  \"model_key\": \"urban_cambridge\",\n  \"source_epsg\": null,\n  \"params\": {\n    \"tile_size\": 10,\n    \"buffer\": 10,\n    \"iou_threshold\": 0.9,\n    \"conf_threshold\": 0.85,\n    \"k_list\": [2, 4, 6, 8, 10],\n    \"pca_components\": 50,\n    \"batch_size\": 16,\n    \"img_size\": 224,\n    \"model_name\": \"vit_base_patch14_dinov2.lvd142m\"\n  }\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/projects",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "v1",
                "projects"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Create a new project.\n\n`model_key` (top-level) selects the **detector** - the Detectree2 .pth weights used for crown detection (Step 0). Valid values: urban_cambridge (default), paracou, randresize. See 'List detectors'.\n\n`params.model_name` selects the **DINOv2 feature-extractor** used for clustering (Step 1B). It is validated against an allowlist - valid values: vit_small_patch14_dinov2.lvd142m, vit_base_patch14_dinov2.lvd142m (default), vit_large_patch14_dinov2.lvd142m. See 'List feature-extractors'. An unknown model_name returns 400 here (it no longer fails mid-pipeline). Omit it to use the default.\n\n`source_epsg` can be null - it's auto-detected from the GeoTIFF on upload.\n\nThe test script saves the returned `project_id` into the environment so later requests can reference {{project_id}}."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "List projects",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/projects",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "v1",
                "projects"
              ]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get project",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/projects/{{project_id}}",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "v1",
                "projects",
                "{{project_id}}"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Full project state, params, orthos, recommended_k, available_k, error message if any."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Delete project",
          "request": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/projects/{{project_id}}",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "v1",
                "projects",
                "{{project_id}}"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Deletes the DB row and the per-project storage directory. 204 No Content on success."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Uploads",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Upload orthomosaic (.tif)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "body": {
              "mode": "formdata",
              "formdata": [
                {
                  "key": "file",
                  "type": "file",
                  "src": [],
                  "description": "Pick a .tif or .tiff GeoTIFF. For the bundled sample use examples/S3C.tif. Call this endpoint repeatedly for a multi-ortho project."
                }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/projects/{{project_id}}/orthomosaic",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "v1",
                "projects",
                "{{project_id}}",
                "orthomosaic"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Streams the file to <storage>/<project_id>/input/ortho/. Returns the refreshed ProjectOut."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Upload orthomosaic from URL (Google Drive)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"url\": \"https://drive.google.com/file/d/<FILE_ID>/view?usp=sharing\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/projects/{{project_id}}/orthomosaic/from-url",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "v1",
                "projects",
                "{{project_id}}",
                "orthomosaic",
                "from-url"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Alternative to the multipart upload: the server downloads the GeoTIFF from a PUBLIC Google Drive share link ('anyone with the link'). Synchronous - blocks for the download, so set a long read timeout for large orthos. Only drive.google.com links are accepted; the file is size-capped and validated as a GeoTIFF. Replaces any previously-registered ortho."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Upload ground-truth (.zip)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "body": {
              "mode": "formdata",
              "formdata": [
                {
                  "key": "file",
                  "type": "file",
                  "src": [],
                  "description": "Zip whose top-level folders are species names containing crown .tif files (the structure step3_validate expects). Optional — needed only if you want validation metrics."
                }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/projects/{{project_id}}/ground-truth",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "v1",
                "projects",
                "{{project_id}}",
                "ground-truth"
              ]
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Analyze (Phase A)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Start analyze (detect + cluster)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "    const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "    if (body.job_id) {",
                  "        pm.environment.set('job_id', body.job_id);",
                  "        console.log('Saved job_id =', body.job_id);",
                  "    }",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/projects/{{project_id}}/analyze",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "v1",
                "projects",
                "{{project_id}}",
                "analyze"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Queues Job A (Detectree2 + DINOv2 features + multi-k clustering + t-SNE) on the `gpu` Celery queue. Requires the project to be in state UPLOADED, AWAITING_LABELS, or FAILED. On success the project transitions to ANALYZING.\n\nThe test script saves the returned `job_id` into the environment."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Poll job status",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/jobs/{{job_id}}",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "v1",
                "jobs",
                "{{job_id}}"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Returns state (QUEUED | STARTED | SUCCEEDED | FAILED), current_stage, progress (0..1), the last 40 log lines, and any error. Repeat until state is SUCCEEDED or FAILED."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Clustering Review",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Clustering overview",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "    const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "    const k = body.recommended_k || (body.available_k && body.available_k[0]);",
                  "    if (k) {",
                  "        pm.environment.set('chosen_k', String(k));",
                  "        console.log('Saved chosen_k =', k);",
                  "    }",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/projects/{{project_id}}/clustering",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "v1",
                "projects",
                "{{project_id}}",
                "clustering"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Returns available_k, recommended_k, the k_recommendation_table (silhouette / DB / inertia per k), and URLs to the k-selection plot, per-k t-SNE plots, and per-cluster crown thumbnails. Project must be AWAITING_LABELS or later."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "k-selection plot (PNG)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/projects/{{project_id}}/clustering/k-selection.png",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "v1",
                "projects",
                "{{project_id}}",
                "clustering",
                "k-selection.png"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Elbow / silhouette / Davies-Bouldin curves across all k. Click 'Save Response → Save to a file' in Postman to download."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "t-SNE for chosen_k (PNG)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/projects/{{project_id}}/clustering/{{chosen_k}}/tsne.png",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "v1",
                "projects",
                "{{project_id}}",
                "clustering",
                "{{chosen_k}}",
                "tsne.png"
              ]
            },
            "description": "2-D t-SNE scatter colored by cluster id for k = {{chosen_k}}."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Clusters with sample crowns",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "    const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "    const cluster = (body.clusters || []).find(c => c.sample_crowns && c.sample_crowns.length);",
                  "    if (cluster) {",
                  "        const url = cluster.sample_crowns[0];",
                  "        const imageName = url.split('/').pop();",
                  "        pm.environment.set('crown_image_name', imageName);",
                  "        console.log('Saved crown_image_name =', imageName);",
                  "    }",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/projects/{{project_id}}/clustering/{{chosen_k}}/clusters?samples=8",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "v1",
                "projects",
                "{{project_id}}",
                "clustering",
                "{{chosen_k}}",
                "clusters"
              ],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "samples",
                  "value": "8",
                  "description": "How many sample crown URLs to include per cluster."
                }
              ]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Crown image (PNG)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/projects/{{project_id}}/crowns/{{crown_image_name}}",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "v1",
                "projects",
                "{{project_id}}",
                "crowns",
                "{{crown_image_name}}"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Render a single crown .tif as PNG. Set crown_image_name to a filename returned by the clusters endpoint."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Detection overlay (PNG)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/projects/{{project_id}}/detection/overlay.png",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "v1",
                "projects",
                "{{project_id}}",
                "detection",
                "overlay.png"
              ],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "stem",
                  "value": "",
                  "description": "With multiple orthos, pass the file stem to pick which overlay.",
                  "disabled": true
                }
              ]
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Labels",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Submit cluster -> species labels",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "    const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "    if (body.chosen_k) {",
                  "        pm.environment.set('chosen_k', body.chosen_k);",
                  "        console.log('Saved chosen_k =', body.chosen_k);",
                  "    }",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"chosen_k\": {{chosen_k}},\n  \"mapping\": [\n    { \"cluster\": 0, \"species\": \"acacia\",     \"notes\": \"\" },\n    { \"cluster\": 1, \"species\": \"non_acacia\", \"notes\": \"\" },\n    { \"cluster\": 2, \"species\": \"acacia\",     \"notes\": \"\" },\n    { \"cluster\": 3, \"species\": \"non_acacia\", \"notes\": \"\" },\n    { \"cluster\": 4, \"species\": \"acacia\",     \"notes\": \"\" },\n    { \"cluster\": 5, \"species\": \"non_acacia\", \"notes\": \"\" }\n  ]\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/projects/{{project_id}}/labels",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "v1",
                "projects",
                "{{project_id}}",
                "labels"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Close the human-in-the-loop gate. chosen_k must be one of available_k. mapping must contain one entry per cluster (0..chosen_k-1). Project transitions to LABELS_SUBMITTED."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Finalize (Phase B)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Start finalize (assign + validate + export)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "    const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "    if (body.job_id) {",
                  "        pm.environment.set('job_id', body.job_id);",
                  "        console.log('Saved job_id =', body.job_id);",
                  "    }",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/projects/{{project_id}}/finalize",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "v1",
                "projects",
                "{{project_id}}",
                "finalize"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Queues Job B on the cpu queue. Requires state LABELS_SUBMITTED, COMPLETED, or FAILED. Overwrites job_id env var so the Poll-job request works for Phase B too."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
